# Machine-generated, never committed:
#   corpus/    – working corpus grown by `cargo fuzz run` (coverage-increasing inputs)
#   artifacts/ – crash / timeout / OOM reproducers
#   coverage/  – `cargo fuzz coverage` output
#   target/    – build artifacts
# Curated, read-only seed inputs live in `seeds/<target>/` and ARE tracked.
#
# Local fuzzing keeps the grown corpus separate from the seeds, e.g.:
#   cargo fuzz run rapdu_unwrap fuzz/corpus/rapdu_unwrap fuzz/seeds/rapdu_unwrap
# (first dir = writable working corpus, rest = read-only seeds). Run
# `cargo fuzz cmin <target> fuzz/corpus/<target>` periodically to keep it small.
/corpus/
/artifacts/
/coverage/
/target/
Cargo.lock
